d 'FOURIERUR': module for Flexible Fourier Form unit root and stationarity tests
d
d	fourierur is the single main command of the fourierur
d package.  It provides a unified    interface to six Fourier-based
d unit root and stationarity tests that use a Flexible	  Fourier
d Form (FFF) to approximate unknown smooth structural breaks.	
d With test(name) you pick one test to run; with test(all) (the
d default) it runs all six    tests sequentially and prints a
d comparative summary. Each test can also still be called   
d directly by name — see the links at the top of the help file. 
d
d KW: unit root
d KW: flexible Fourier form
d
d Requires: Stata version 14 
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260716
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f fourierur.ado
f fourierdf.sthlp
f fourierdf.ado
f fourierdfdf.ado
f fourierfffff.ado
f fouriergls.ado
f fourierkpss.ado
f fourierlm.ado
f fourierdfdf.sthlp
f fourierfffff.sthlp
f fouriergls.sthlp
f fourierkpss.sthlp
f fourierlm.sthlp
f fourierur.sthlp
f fourierur_example.do
